From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Add explicit ghc-pkg recache after Cabal register for Stage0 packages

When using a different bootstrap GHC version (e.g., 9.6.7 to build 9.2.8),
Cabal's register command doesn't properly update the package database cache.

The issue is:
1. cabal copy --target-package-db puts the .conf file in the correct location
2. cabal register is supposed to register the package but doesn't update
   the package.cache file properly
3. Subsequent configure steps can't find the newly registered package

The fix adds an explicit ghc-pkg recache call after Cabal.registerPackage
for Stage0 packages. This ensures the package.cache file is updated and
the package becomes visible to ghc-pkg queries.

Note: GhcPkg Init actually does 'ghc-pkg recache' (see GhcPkg.hs comment).
We reuse it here to update the cache after registration.

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
@@ -143,6 +143,13 @@ buildConf _ context@Context {..} _conf = do
     -- Copy and register the package.
     Cabal.copyPackage context
     Cabal.registerPackage context
+
+    -- Explicitly recache the package database after registration.
+    -- Cabal's register command doesn't always update the package.cache file
+    -- properly, especially when using a different bootstrap GHC version.
+    -- GhcPkg Init actually does 'ghc-pkg recache' (see GhcPkg.hs).
+    when (stage == Stage0) $
+        build $ target context (GhcPkg Init stage) [] []

     -- We declare that this rule also produces files matching:
     --   <root>/stage<N>/lib/<arch>-<os>-ghc-<version>/*libHS<pkgid>*
